WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:45.003 --> 00:00:46.463
Let's go. Let's go.

3
00:00:53.595 --> 00:00:56.473
Hey! The machine's broken.

4
00:00:56.556 --> 00:00:58.267
I want my $40.

5
00:00:59.184 --> 00:01:00.852
Come on. I can see you in there.

6
00:01:02.354 --> 00:01:03.355
Come on.

7
00:01:05.899 --> 00:01:07.067
Hey.

8
00:01:13.240 --> 00:01:15.367
Come on. I can see you in there.

9
00:01:16.910 --> 00:01:18.620
Oof! For 40 bucks.

10
00:01:19.955 --> 00:01:22.624
You okay. Mr. Price?

11
00:01:22.708 --> 00:01:24.167
Why did this happen at my branch?

12
00:01:24.251 --> 00:01:25.377
This is so unfair.

13
00:01:25.460 --> 00:01:27.296
I'm sure the dead guy feels the same.

14
00:01:29.256 --> 00:01:30.257
Here. take a seat.

15
00:01:30.340 --> 00:01:32.801
The camera on the ATM
is the only video feed they didn't cut.

16
00:01:32.884 --> 00:01:35.178
Yeah. they took out
the phone lines and the Wi-Fi too.

17
00:01:35.262 --> 00:01:37.180
That's why the gunshots
didn't trigger the alarm.

18
00:01:37.264 --> 00:01:41.101
Okay. Mr. Price. can you show us…

19
00:01:42.144 --> 00:01:43.937
Okay. yeah. You just keep doing that.

20
00:01:44.021 --> 00:01:46.023
We're gonna take a look around.

21
00:01:46.106 --> 00:01:47.566
No footage from inside the bank.

22
00:01:47.649 --> 00:01:48.734
No fingerprints yet.

23
00:01:48.817 --> 00:01:50.152
And our only witness is dead.

24
00:01:55.282 --> 00:01:56.283
Huh.

25
00:02:00.454 --> 00:02:01.913
Whoa. That's weird.

26
00:02:01.997 --> 00:02:03.832
- What's weird?
- The chemo.

27
00:02:03.915 --> 00:02:06.543
It made my vision dull. kind of blurry.

28
00:02:06.626 --> 00:02:09.880
But now that that's over.
everything's a lot clearer.

29
00:02:09.963 --> 00:02:12.132
I can see better than I could
before the cancer.

30
00:02:14.301 --> 00:02:15.636
What if it's a superpower?

31
00:02:16.762 --> 00:02:18.555
What if it's normal eyesight?

32
00:02:19.514 --> 00:02:22.059
Okay. Bring your mere
mortal eyeballs over here.

33
00:02:22.893 --> 00:02:24.269
Take a look at these boxes.

34
00:02:25.228 --> 00:02:26.605
It's the locks. They're different.

35
00:02:26.688 --> 00:02:28.190
- You see that?
- Oh. wow.

36
00:02:28.273 --> 00:02:33.236
Okay. so they broke into this one.
took the contents. replaced the lock.

37
00:02:34.237 --> 00:02:35.656
The bank didn't even notice.

38
00:02:36.156 --> 00:02:38.909
That's an archvillain move right there.

39
00:02:39.409 --> 00:02:42.162
Hey. Price. Price.

40
00:02:42.245 --> 00:02:44.915
What now?

41
00:02:44.998 --> 00:02:47.501
This safe deposit box.
I need the name and address of its owner.

42
00:02:47.584 --> 00:02:51.004
Oh. I am not permitted
to release that information

43
00:02:51.088 --> 00:02:52.506
without the client's approval.

44
00:02:53.090 --> 00:02:55.425
You know
we're investigating a robbery. right?

45
00:02:55.509 --> 00:02:57.260
I'm sorry. but it is policy.

46
00:02:57.886 --> 00:02:59.304
- Never mind.
- We'll get a warrant.

47
00:03:07.437 --> 00:03:11.191
Let us help you find
what you're longing for.

48
00:03:11.775 --> 00:03:14.403
your ideal life partner.

49
00:03:15.570 --> 00:03:19.866
Jennings Luxury.
For your happily ever after.

50
00:03:20.367 --> 00:03:22.244
Whole lot
of powerful Atlanta names

51
00:03:22.327 --> 00:03:25.747
use this matchmaking service.
What ever happened to just meeting people?

52
00:03:25.831 --> 00:03:27.207
You know. chance encounters?

53
00:03:27.290 --> 00:03:29.000
I've actually been
researching hermit life.

54
00:03:29.084 --> 00:03:31.711
It's a whole movement. Want me
to send you some information? I can...

55
00:03:31.795 --> 00:03:33.046
- No.
- Get on with it.

56
00:03:33.547 --> 00:03:34.840
Fine.

57
00:03:34.923 --> 00:03:37.759
One perforating gunshot
entered the right arm back here.

58
00:03:37.843 --> 00:03:40.262
exited the front here.
Four more to his chest.

59
00:03:40.345 --> 00:03:42.097
So someone shot him with his back turned.

60
00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:44.641
He spun around.
They finished it. plus some.

61
00:03:44.724 --> 00:03:46.101
This happened outside his home?

62
00:03:46.184 --> 00:03:48.270
No apparent robbery. No witnesses.

63
00:03:48.770 --> 00:03:50.439
Could have been a disgruntled client.

64
00:03:51.648 --> 00:03:56.486
All these women seem identical.
Like to travel. live an active lifestyle.

65
00:03:56.570 --> 00:03:59.156
Why are so many of them event planners?

66
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.782
They just throw parties?

67
00:04:00.866 --> 00:04:02.617
What is that? Like a brand ambassador?

68
00:04:02.701 --> 00:04:04.995
- I thought that was an influencer.
- Whatever the job is.

69
00:04:05.078 --> 00:04:08.290
it's vague enough they probably don't
get asked too many follow-up questions.

70
00:04:08.373 --> 00:04:11.001
I do like that.
I can't have another man ask me

71
00:04:11.084 --> 00:04:14.004
to fix a parking ticket
when he finds out I am GBI.

72
00:04:14.087 --> 00:04:17.215
You telling these men your government name
and where you work?

73
00:04:17.299 --> 00:04:19.301
- For the government?
- That's a good point.

74
00:04:19.384 --> 00:04:21.428
Okay.

75
00:04:21.511 --> 00:04:23.430
Ah! The business partner is here.

76
00:04:24.806 --> 00:04:28.560
Ms. Summermann.
we pulled Mr. Jennings's phone records.

77
00:04:28.643 --> 00:04:31.396
He made several calls to you
in the hours before he died.

78
00:04:32.564 --> 00:04:34.524
Sawyer and I talked all the time.

79
00:04:35.567 --> 00:04:36.985
Mostly business.

80
00:04:37.068 --> 00:04:38.153
And we're friends.

81
00:04:38.236 --> 00:04:39.738
Well. I have to ask.

82
00:04:40.322 --> 00:04:42.449
last night.
where were you between 7:00 and 8:00?

83
00:04:42.532 --> 00:04:45.118
I take a 7:00 spin class.

84
00:04:45.202 --> 00:04:47.162
BLUEGYM in Piedmont.

85
00:04:47.245 --> 00:04:51.792
Did you and Mr. Jennings have any
disagreements lately? Personal? Financial?

86
00:04:51.875 --> 00:04:52.876
None.

87
00:04:53.752 --> 00:04:57.130
I mean. I don't mean to sound callous.
but the company has never been better.

88
00:04:57.214 --> 00:04:58.507
What about the members?

89
00:04:59.341 --> 00:05:01.510
Were any of them unhappy with the service?

90
00:05:02.511 --> 00:05:05.931
If a date isn't a match.
we work with the client to make it right.

91
00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:08.266
Just curious.

92
00:05:08.850 --> 00:05:12.187
you charge male clients
$50.000 for a membership.

93
00:05:12.270 --> 00:05:13.647
and women only pay five.

94
00:05:14.689 --> 00:05:16.274
Men aren't angry about that?

95
00:05:16.358 --> 00:05:20.570
It's standard practice
in high-end matchmaking services.

96
00:05:21.988 --> 00:05:25.700
If you weren't to charge the women.
it could seem like prostitution too. huh?

97
00:05:28.286 --> 00:05:30.455
Yes. we charge a steep fee.

98
00:05:30.539 --> 00:05:35.877
but some people are willing to pay
any price to find that one great love.

99
00:05:36.837 --> 00:05:41.299
My work is bringing people together.
helping them find joy.

100
00:05:43.802 --> 00:05:47.430
Ms. Summermann. I'm gonna need
the contact information for your clients.

101
00:05:47.514 --> 00:05:50.767
I hope you find
the monster that took Sawyer from us.

102
00:05:50.851 --> 00:05:56.147
And… maybe I can help you find your joy.

103
00:06:03.822 --> 00:06:08.285
I don't need your help
because I have a date.

104
00:06:15.667 --> 00:06:18.712
"See you soon."

105
00:06:18.795 --> 00:06:22.507
"If I get a parking ticket.
can you help me out?"

106
00:06:27.220 --> 00:06:28.263
"Sorry.

107
00:06:28.346 --> 00:06:31.933
Killed in the line of duty.
Reservation canceled."

108
00:06:33.101 --> 00:06:34.728
And blocked.

109
00:06:36.229 --> 00:06:37.230
- Hey.
- Yeah?

110
00:06:37.314 --> 00:06:42.485
Can I get a gin martini.
extra dirty. extra gin?

111
00:06:54.664 --> 00:06:59.252
I don't wanna be that dude.
but I'm gonna be that dude.

112
00:07:00.754 --> 00:07:03.548
You are stunning.

113
00:07:05.884 --> 00:07:08.637
Any way you'd say yes
if I asked to sit with you?

114
00:07:10.055 --> 00:07:11.931
Everything you just said was

115
00:07:12.932 --> 00:07:14.643
so hypothetical.

116
00:07:18.063 --> 00:07:19.648
Ouch. Right. right. right. right.

117
00:07:19.731 --> 00:07:23.026
I-I should just ask. huh?

118
00:07:23.109 --> 00:07:24.110
Or you could just sit.

119
00:07:26.905 --> 00:07:29.741
- Great.
- You know. I'd say good.

120
00:07:29.824 --> 00:07:31.326
I don't know about great yet.

121
00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:35.163
When does this snark wear off?

122
00:07:35.246 --> 00:07:36.414
I'm just curious.

123
00:07:37.123 --> 00:07:38.124
This will help.

124
00:07:44.297 --> 00:07:45.382
I'm Malcolm.

125
00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.634
I didn't even ask for your name.
I'm sorry.

126
00:07:50.095 --> 00:07:51.221
Amanda.

127
00:07:51.971 --> 00:07:53.181
I'm an event planner.

128
00:07:53.264 --> 00:07:58.728
Okay. so about weather.
common interests. world peace. no?

129
00:07:58.812 --> 00:08:00.355
You just jump right to your job title.

130
00:08:01.690 --> 00:08:04.776
- You must be a Leo.
- I'm sorry. my bad.

131
00:08:04.859 --> 00:08:07.195
I assumed
that I was talking to a grown man.

132
00:08:07.779 --> 00:08:10.281
You know. I haven't met
an astrology buff since…

133
00:08:11.783 --> 00:08:13.159
high school.

134
00:08:14.536 --> 00:08:16.663
Oh. Ouch.

135
00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:19.916
Did I just play myself?

136
00:08:20.834 --> 00:08:22.544
Let's have this one drink and see.

137
00:08:26.589 --> 00:08:27.590
I can do that.

138
00:08:30.593 --> 00:08:31.594
Cheers.

139
00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:35.807
You think I'm feisty?

140
00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:38.435
What? You don't think you…

141
00:08:38.518 --> 00:08:41.396
Okay. all right.
you know what? I'm-I'm so sorry.

142
00:08:41.479 --> 00:08:43.148
I was just kidding. I was just kidding.

143
00:08:43.231 --> 00:08:45.984
You know what? It's fine.
because. yeah. I'm a Leo.

144
00:08:46.067 --> 00:08:47.152
so it's fine.

145
00:08:47.235 --> 00:08:48.403
- Mm-hmm.
- It's okay.

146
00:08:48.987 --> 00:08:50.697
I do feel bad though.

147
00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:53.658
We're keeping the waitstaff
here so late.

148
00:08:55.493 --> 00:08:58.496
Sorry if this is too forward. but…

149
00:09:00.373 --> 00:09:03.835
I do have a room here at the hotel.

150
00:09:17.599 --> 00:09:20.268
Okay. okay. maybe hold on.

151
00:09:20.351 --> 00:09:21.519
Um…

152
00:09:21.603 --> 00:09:23.313
I'm not saying stop.

153
00:09:23.396 --> 00:09:26.649
I'm just saying that we've only known
each other for three hours. so…

154
00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:29.027
- Mm-hmm. Okay. Um. hmm.
- Yeah.

155
00:09:29.110 --> 00:09:30.862
- Medical issues?
- Diabetes.

156
00:09:30.945 --> 00:09:32.238
- Good to know.
- Allergies?

157
00:09:32.322 --> 00:09:34.741
- Wasp. Favorite movie?
- Say Anything. Have you seen it?

158
00:09:34.824 --> 00:09:36.201
Uh. maybe a long time ago.

159
00:09:36.284 --> 00:09:38.286
Do you have
any outstanding parking tickets?

160
00:09:38.369 --> 00:09:39.579
I have a driver.

161
00:09:39.662 --> 00:09:40.955
Family? Where did you grow up?

162
00:09:41.039 --> 00:09:42.749
- You know what?
- Mm.

163
00:09:42.832 --> 00:09:44.667
- I think that is good enough.
- Okay.

164
00:10:08.108 --> 00:10:09.692
- Amanda.
- No.

165
00:10:39.556 --> 00:10:41.015
Nice to meet you. Malcolm.

166
00:11:00.201 --> 00:11:01.703
The site sounds perfect.

167
00:11:04.497 --> 00:11:08.459
All right. Well. send me the specs
and we'll see if we can make it work.

168
00:11:10.086 --> 00:11:11.087
All right.

169
00:11:12.463 --> 00:11:13.464
Bye.

170
00:11:14.507 --> 00:11:16.926
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

171
00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:18.303
- Hey.
- Hey.

172
00:11:22.557 --> 00:11:24.017
Ooh.

173
00:11:25.059 --> 00:11:27.061
I'm sorry.
I just had to take care of a few things.

174
00:11:27.145 --> 00:11:29.981
No. you're good. You're very good.

175
00:11:32.192 --> 00:11:33.359
You know…

176
00:11:34.068 --> 00:11:35.778
…during our little Q and A last night.

177
00:11:35.862 --> 00:11:38.323
I forgot the most important question.

178
00:11:38.406 --> 00:11:39.407
Oh?

179
00:11:40.658 --> 00:11:43.953
Are you a coffee or tea person?

180
00:11:44.037 --> 00:11:47.373
So. I just got a little of everything.

181
00:11:47.457 --> 00:11:52.462
You sure did. and I wish that I would have
taken that apple tart to go last night.

182
00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:54.505
It would've been amazing right now.

183
00:11:54.589 --> 00:11:57.800
Well. I can call down and have
the pastry chef whip one up for you.

184
00:11:57.884 --> 00:12:00.803
I'm pretty sure
the restaurant's not open this early.

185
00:12:01.387 --> 00:12:03.473
They'll do it for me. It's my restaurant.

186
00:12:04.390 --> 00:12:07.227
You know. that's cute.

187
00:12:07.310 --> 00:12:10.146
but the restaurant's connected
to the hotel. so…

188
00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:11.272
- It is.
- Hmm.

189
00:12:11.356 --> 00:12:13.149
I also own the hotel.

190
00:12:16.027 --> 00:12:17.028
Hmm.

191
00:12:17.987 --> 00:12:20.240
"Hmm"? Oh. you don't believe me?

192
00:12:20.323 --> 00:12:22.408
- I didn't say that.
- All right. look it up.

193
00:12:22.492 --> 00:12:23.743
The Quinton Atlanta.

194
00:12:23.826 --> 00:12:25.036
Oh. I know where we are.

195
00:12:25.119 --> 00:12:27.247
Go ahead. I'll wait.

196
00:12:29.874 --> 00:12:30.875
Mm.

197
00:12:33.503 --> 00:12:36.506
- Oh. my God.
- Mm-hmm.

198
00:12:36.589 --> 00:12:38.758
You wouldn't believe
how many times this has happened to me.

199
00:12:38.841 --> 00:12:43.388
Honestly. if I accidentally sleep
with one more millionaire…

200
00:12:43.471 --> 00:12:44.472
Mm.

201
00:12:45.306 --> 00:12:46.724
- Well. look.
- Hmm?

202
00:12:47.517 --> 00:12:49.852
The kitchen started prepping at 8:00...

203
00:12:49.936 --> 00:12:51.980
- Wait. wait. it's past 8:00?
- Yeah.

204
00:12:52.063 --> 00:12:53.856
- I gotta go.
- What? Wait. wait. wait. Hey. hey. hey.

205
00:12:53.940 --> 00:12:55.775
sure. sure. all right. but…

206
00:12:56.442 --> 00:12:57.694
And when can I see you again?

207
00:12:58.778 --> 00:13:00.613
Actually. that's not what I meant to ask.

208
00:13:00.697 --> 00:13:03.658
Can I see you tonight?

209
00:13:04.534 --> 00:13:07.287
Here. Amanda. put in your number.

210
00:13:19.299 --> 00:13:21.968
…said she was angry crying.
Okay. cool. Thank you.

211
00:13:22.051 --> 00:13:25.263
Oh. hey! Glad you could make it.

212
00:13:25.346 --> 00:13:28.391
Me? I've just been diligently working
while you were. what?

213
00:13:29.183 --> 00:13:31.269
Dancing with temptation. were we?

214
00:13:31.352 --> 00:13:34.022
I held it down here for months
while you went to go find yourself at…

215
00:13:34.105 --> 00:13:35.732
What was the name of that place?

216
00:13:36.232 --> 00:13:37.233
Hypocrite. Tennessee?

217
00:13:37.317 --> 00:13:39.319
That lovely town is Soddy-Daisy.

218
00:13:39.402 --> 00:13:40.903
And you're wearing
the same clothes as yesterday.

219
00:13:40.987 --> 00:13:42.822
Oh. shut up. Nobody's gonna notice.

220
00:13:42.905 --> 00:13:45.700
Oh. Faith. why are you wearing
the same clothes you wore yesterday?

221
00:13:45.783 --> 00:13:47.702
Can everybody stop worrying
about what I'm wearing?

222
00:13:47.785 --> 00:13:50.163
Oh. You had a date last night.

223
00:13:50.246 --> 00:13:51.414
I wasn't gonna say anything.

224
00:13:51.497 --> 00:13:54.459
but I'm pretty sure that's a bra strap
sticking out your purse.

225
00:13:55.293 --> 00:13:57.545
Oh. Lord. Please just tell me
he does not work in this building.

226
00:13:57.628 --> 00:13:59.839
He doesn't even know
that I work in this building.

227
00:13:59.922 --> 00:14:02.800
so there you go.
He thinks I am an event planner.

228
00:14:02.884 --> 00:14:05.470
- Hmm. What name did you use? Beyoncé?
- Mmm.

229
00:14:05.553 --> 00:14:06.637
Sasha?

230
00:14:07.638 --> 00:14:09.307
Shakira?

231
00:14:09.390 --> 00:14:11.893
I always used Simone. She was my old boss.

232
00:14:11.976 --> 00:14:13.144
Mmm.

233
00:14:13.227 --> 00:14:15.813
- What?
- I had to think fast.

234
00:14:15.897 --> 00:14:18.441
Faith Mitchell. you did not use my name!

235
00:14:18.524 --> 00:14:20.318
No. that is not okay and inappropriate.

236
00:14:20.401 --> 00:14:22.153
You were just talking
about my bra in my purse.

237
00:14:22.236 --> 00:14:23.446
And where's the lie?

238
00:14:24.280 --> 00:14:27.366
What did it sound like
when he whispered my name in your ear?

239
00:14:27.450 --> 00:14:29.035
- Ew.
- Gross.

240
00:14:29.118 --> 00:14:32.121
Now.
what's your progress on this case?

241
00:14:32.205 --> 00:14:33.831
Sawyer Jennings's credit card records show

242
00:14:33.915 --> 00:14:36.918
that he went to a diner in Midtown
the night he was killed.

243
00:14:37.001 --> 00:14:38.920
Manager said that he was there
with a woman.

244
00:14:39.003 --> 00:14:40.254
She was angry crying.

245
00:14:40.338 --> 00:14:42.340
Was it Liv Summermann.
his business partner?

246
00:14:42.423 --> 00:14:45.718
Anna Martello. She used a credit card
to buy a drink before Jennings arrived.

247
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:47.220
Let's go pay her a visit.

248
00:14:47.303 --> 00:14:50.890
Wonderful idea.
Thank you. "Amanda chiquita."

249
00:14:50.973 --> 00:14:51.974
That's "little Amanda."

250
00:14:54.060 --> 00:14:57.438
- I did this to myself.
- Sure did.

251
00:15:01.359 --> 00:15:02.777
Sure you don't wanna sit?

252
00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:04.320
No.
Standing's better for my back.

253
00:15:05.363 --> 00:15:09.075
Okay. Price said
First Peachtree Bank lost 500.000 in cash.

254
00:15:09.158 --> 00:15:10.910
It's not a bad haul. but…

255
00:15:10.993 --> 00:15:13.329
…considering the equipment
these guys used to cut into that vault.

256
00:15:13.412 --> 00:15:14.539
these guys are pros.

257
00:15:14.622 --> 00:15:15.998
- That's chump change to them.
- Yeah.

258
00:15:16.082 --> 00:15:20.044
unless what was in
the safe deposit box was worth way more.

259
00:15:20.128 --> 00:15:23.756
You know. it'd be great if the judge
would respond to my warrant request.

260
00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:24.882
You gotta work the clerk.

261
00:15:24.966 --> 00:15:27.301
I am working the clerk.
Let me see the photo.

262
00:15:29.762 --> 00:15:32.765
- That's the burger place up on the corner?
- Yeah. pretty good camera.

263
00:15:32.849 --> 00:15:34.809
Must be why they charge 30 bucks a burger.

264
00:15:34.892 --> 00:15:38.646
Oh. Black sedan. no plates. no faces.

265
00:15:38.729 --> 00:15:41.274
The rear passenger has a huge head.

266
00:15:44.193 --> 00:15:46.904
- That's not his head. that's a mask.
- Animal mask.

267
00:15:46.988 --> 00:15:48.739
Oh. She shifted. I gotta sit.

268
00:15:48.823 --> 00:15:50.032
Oh. yeah. here. here.

269
00:15:50.992 --> 00:15:52.493
All right. So…

270
00:15:53.578 --> 00:15:56.205
…I can add "animal mask" to the search.

271
00:15:57.415 --> 00:15:59.792
Hey. look at that. That did it.

272
00:15:59.876 --> 00:16:03.087
Three similar robberies.
the last three years.

273
00:16:03.171 --> 00:16:06.757
Nashville. Chicago. Oakland.

274
00:16:06.841 --> 00:16:08.885
- Same crew?
- It's hard to say.

275
00:16:08.968 --> 00:16:11.554
These similar robberies were
all of cash management warehouses

276
00:16:11.637 --> 00:16:14.015
and they made off
with 20 to 30 million each.

277
00:16:14.098 --> 00:16:15.850
But only half a mil from here.

278
00:16:15.933 --> 00:16:18.519
They really wanted
what was in that safe deposit box.

279
00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:22.690
Ormewood. I hear you got X-ray vision.
What kind of underwear am I wearing now?

280
00:16:22.773 --> 00:16:24.734
That's a trick question. Don't answer.

281
00:16:24.817 --> 00:16:26.110
Don't mock my superpowers.

282
00:16:26.194 --> 00:16:27.987
Can you fly? Can he fly?

283
00:16:28.070 --> 00:16:31.240
Franklin. get in here! Now!

284
00:16:34.410 --> 00:16:35.828
Um. what do I do?

285
00:16:35.912 --> 00:16:37.830
Oh. Now you want me to be clairvoyant?

286
00:16:37.914 --> 00:16:39.415
Too late.

287
00:16:41.918 --> 00:16:42.919
Good luck.

288
00:16:48.257 --> 00:16:49.258
Oh.

289
00:16:51.844 --> 00:16:53.095
What's up. Cap?

290
00:16:56.515 --> 00:16:58.351
I need your help.

291
00:16:58.434 --> 00:16:59.769
Who is that under the tarp?

292
00:16:59.852 --> 00:17:02.939
It's a surprise for Polaski's kid.

293
00:17:05.399 --> 00:17:06.400
Got her a stroller.

294
00:17:06.484 --> 00:17:07.610
Oh. that is not a stroller.

295
00:17:07.693 --> 00:17:09.654
Oh. it will be after we put it together.

296
00:17:09.737 --> 00:17:12.073
That's crazy. Sounded like you said "we."

297
00:17:14.033 --> 00:17:16.494
Fine. Where's the instruction manual?

298
00:17:16.577 --> 00:17:19.455
Did the cavemen need a manual
when they created fire?

299
00:17:19.538 --> 00:17:21.123
They got ate by dinosaurs.

300
00:17:21.207 --> 00:17:24.168
Did the Mesopotamians need a manual
when they invented the wheel?

301
00:17:24.252 --> 00:17:25.962
They invented it to outrun tuberculosis.

302
00:17:26.045 --> 00:17:27.463
When Thomas Edison invented the lightbulb.

303
00:17:27.546 --> 00:17:29.465
- he didn't have a manual...
- Look. I'ma stop you right there.

304
00:17:29.549 --> 00:17:32.260
He stole that from Lewis Latimer.
and you threw away the manual.

305
00:17:32.343 --> 00:17:33.469
Yes. I did.

306
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.766
So. let's see if we can get
a better shot of our getaway car.

307
00:17:38.849 --> 00:17:41.978
These are from a drugstore
a mile east of the bank.

308
00:17:42.562 --> 00:17:43.729
Black sedan.

309
00:17:44.647 --> 00:17:47.358
- What is that pattern in the rear window?
- The spots?

310
00:17:47.441 --> 00:17:49.068
- Yeah.
- That's a cheetah.

311
00:17:51.821 --> 00:17:53.573
- I gotta pee. Walk with me?
- Yeah.

312
00:17:54.699 --> 00:17:57.868
All right. there's an arm in this photo.

313
00:17:57.952 --> 00:17:59.287
Is that a tattoo?

314
00:17:59.912 --> 00:18:00.913
Could be a mole.

315
00:18:00.997 --> 00:18:02.957
- It could be a tattoo of a mole.
- Mmm.

316
00:18:03.040 --> 00:18:04.584
Hey. Mishi's froggy.

317
00:18:05.751 --> 00:18:09.171
- Come again?
- Yeah. Mishi. she's an ATL tattoo legend.

318
00:18:09.255 --> 00:18:10.965
Yeah. that frog's her signature.

319
00:18:11.465 --> 00:18:14.677
How can you not know Mishi?
What have you been doing with your lives?

320
00:18:14.760 --> 00:18:16.304
Not getting arrested.

321
00:18:16.387 --> 00:18:18.139
- Oh. okay.
- Thank you. sir.

322
00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:24.228
- Uh. Mishi. heard she's a legend.
- Oh.

323
00:18:26.647 --> 00:18:30.276
Well. people pay Jennings big money
to find their perfect life partner.

324
00:18:30.359 --> 00:18:32.987
all the while he's in a toxic relationship
with Anna Martello.

325
00:18:33.070 --> 00:18:36.115
The number of gunshots does point
to his death being a crime of passion.

326
00:18:36.907 --> 00:18:39.619
- Speaking of passion...
- Don't you say passion!

327
00:18:39.702 --> 00:18:42.079
I won't kiss and tell.
and I don't need any dating advice.

328
00:18:42.163 --> 00:18:45.333
Okay. you're right. I mean. it's obvious
you got this all under control. Amanda.

329
00:18:45.416 --> 00:18:48.210
Uh. what is there to have under control?
It was one night. that's all.

330
00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:49.378
You know. I agree.

331
00:18:49.462 --> 00:18:50.921
Not everything has to be so serious.

332
00:18:51.005 --> 00:18:53.758
Someone told me that recently. and they…

333
00:18:53.841 --> 00:18:55.718
she… they have a point.

334
00:18:55.801 --> 00:18:57.928
Was it Ava? Was Ava the they/she/they?

335
00:18:58.012 --> 00:18:59.513
By the way.
I knew that you slept with her.

336
00:18:59.597 --> 00:19:01.349
I just know how to mind my business.

337
00:19:01.432 --> 00:19:02.433
Mm-hmm.

338
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:05.186
Anna Martello.

339
00:19:06.520 --> 00:19:07.813
No. no. no. no.

340
00:19:07.897 --> 00:19:09.273
Hey. GBI. Hey. Anna!

341
00:19:09.357 --> 00:19:11.025
- Ms. Martello. don't run. We just…
- Help!

342
00:19:11.108 --> 00:19:13.152
- …need to ask you a few questions about…
- Help me!

343
00:19:13.235 --> 00:19:15.071
Please don't.

344
00:19:15.154 --> 00:19:17.698
He sent you to kill me. didn't he?

345
00:19:18.407 --> 00:19:19.450
Who?

346
00:19:26.499 --> 00:19:27.667
I'm being followed.

347
00:19:29.001 --> 00:19:30.586
I know I sound paranoid. but it's true.

348
00:19:30.670 --> 00:19:33.714
I've been staying with my sister.
I came back to get some clothes.

349
00:19:33.798 --> 00:19:35.341
and you were at my door and…

350
00:19:36.717 --> 00:19:38.928
I thought he sent you
to kill me like he killed Sawyer.

351
00:19:39.637 --> 00:19:41.263
I need you to give me a name.

352
00:19:46.268 --> 00:19:47.436
Brody Evans.

353
00:19:48.771 --> 00:19:50.481
Three weeks ago. we went on a date.

354
00:19:51.273 --> 00:19:52.400
A match.

355
00:19:52.483 --> 00:19:54.402
- Through Jennings Luxury?
- Yeah.

356
00:19:55.695 --> 00:19:57.154
Brody's family is old money.

357
00:19:57.238 --> 00:19:59.990
He owns his own tech firm.

358
00:20:00.074 --> 00:20:01.701
We got drinks.

359
00:20:01.784 --> 00:20:02.785
I blacked out.

360
00:20:03.994 --> 00:20:05.705
Or that's what Brody said happened.

361
00:20:05.788 --> 00:20:06.956
Were you…

362
00:20:09.166 --> 00:20:10.167
hurt?

363
00:20:13.546 --> 00:20:16.590
Brody threatened me
if I talked to the police…

364
00:20:18.300 --> 00:20:19.468
And his family?

365
00:20:20.469 --> 00:20:23.597
I can't afford that-that fight.

366
00:20:26.892 --> 00:20:29.729
But the one thing I could do…

367
00:20:31.814 --> 00:20:34.817
was make sure other women
weren't handed over to that creep.

368
00:20:36.110 --> 00:20:38.195
I told Sawyer the day after it happened.

369
00:20:38.279 --> 00:20:42.992
He promised me
that Brody would be dropped as a client.

370
00:20:44.118 --> 00:20:45.661
This is three weeks ago?

371
00:20:47.580 --> 00:20:51.083
Anna. you saw Sawyer
one hour before he was killed.

372
00:20:51.167 --> 00:20:54.754
There was a witness at the diner
that overheard you yelling at him. Why?

373
00:20:54.837 --> 00:20:58.174
Because Jennings Luxury
posted photos from their monthly mixer.

374
00:20:59.091 --> 00:21:02.178
I wasn't invited but Brody was.

375
00:21:03.012 --> 00:21:04.889
He was smiling.

376
00:21:04.972 --> 00:21:08.642
He had his arm wrapped around
some poor woman. I was livid.

377
00:21:08.726 --> 00:21:10.352
What was Sawyer's response?

378
00:21:11.061 --> 00:21:12.313
He didn't know.

379
00:21:14.440 --> 00:21:15.983
I believed him.

380
00:21:18.194 --> 00:21:20.613
So. he called Brody.

381
00:21:20.696 --> 00:21:22.156
While you were at the diner?

382
00:21:22.239 --> 00:21:23.741
Right in front of me.

383
00:21:23.824 --> 00:21:25.451
He said he knew about the assault

384
00:21:26.035 --> 00:21:29.079
and that he would tell everyone in Atlanta
that Brody was a monster.

385
00:21:33.375 --> 00:21:35.211
I can put you on Mishi's wait-list.

386
00:21:35.294 --> 00:21:38.255
How's April…

387
00:21:40.174 --> 00:21:41.217
2028?

388
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:43.302
- For a frog?
- Yeah.

389
00:21:45.179 --> 00:21:47.264
Mishi. Hi.

390
00:21:47.348 --> 00:21:49.809
Detective Polaski.
This is Detective Ormewood.

391
00:21:50.684 --> 00:21:51.685
We spoke.

392
00:21:51.769 --> 00:21:53.479
That's a lot of canvas.

393
00:21:55.815 --> 00:21:57.399
- Thank you.
- You want to show her the photo?

394
00:21:57.483 --> 00:21:58.484
Yep.

395
00:22:00.903 --> 00:22:01.904
It's mine.

396
00:22:02.488 --> 00:22:03.864
Photo's crap.

397
00:22:05.658 --> 00:22:06.909
See here.

398
00:22:06.992 --> 00:22:10.079
- this is my signature on the leaf.
- Great.

399
00:22:10.162 --> 00:22:12.164
We're going to need
his name and contact information

400
00:22:12.248 --> 00:22:13.290
if you have that on file.

401
00:22:13.374 --> 00:22:15.209
Ooh. I'm discreet.

402
00:22:15.292 --> 00:22:17.169
No paperwork. cash and crypto only.

403
00:22:19.505 --> 00:22:22.383
You didn't happen to do
this other tattoo of his. did you?

404
00:22:22.466 --> 00:22:25.719
I don't do mom tattoos.

405
00:22:27.096 --> 00:22:29.306
Well. look at that. He has a mom.

406
00:22:30.516 --> 00:22:33.102
My client was enjoying
a concert at City Stage.

407
00:22:33.185 --> 00:22:36.939
- My boy Jelly Roll. Great seats.
- According to phone records.

408
00:22:37.022 --> 00:22:40.651
you were one of the last people
Sawyer Jennings talked to before he died.

409
00:22:41.777 --> 00:22:43.153
What did you two talk about?

410
00:22:43.237 --> 00:22:44.989
He was following up
to see how a date went.

411
00:22:45.489 --> 00:22:47.992
I pay top dollar.
so they want to keep me happy.

412
00:22:48.909 --> 00:22:50.786
I'm still looking for my Amal Clooney.

413
00:22:50.870 --> 00:22:52.121
She's so exotic.

414
00:22:53.581 --> 00:22:55.374
Now. was the follow-up part
of that phone call

415
00:22:55.457 --> 00:23:00.421
before or after Mr. Jennings threatened to
expose you for date-raping Anna Martello?

416
00:23:00.504 --> 00:23:01.630
Oh. come on.

417
00:23:01.714 --> 00:23:04.258
My client has an alibi
for the night of Mr. Jennings's death.

418
00:23:04.341 --> 00:23:06.969
That's why we're here.
If some random woman wants to accuse him...

419
00:23:07.052 --> 00:23:09.722
You can say her name. Anna Martello.

420
00:23:09.805 --> 00:23:13.142
Unless she wants to provide evidence
and bring a formal complaint.

421
00:23:13.225 --> 00:23:14.894
you're not to harass my client again.

422
00:23:19.064 --> 00:23:20.357
What time was that concert?

423
00:23:21.609 --> 00:23:23.861
7:00. I left around midnight.

424
00:23:23.944 --> 00:23:25.070
You sure?

425
00:23:26.113 --> 00:23:29.158
I'm asking because Atlanta's
the most surveilled city in the nation.

426
00:23:32.912 --> 00:23:35.331
I'ma scour through every bit
of that footage.

427
00:23:36.415 --> 00:23:40.836
Follow your every step
to find a hole in your alibi.

428
00:23:41.921 --> 00:23:43.213
We're done here.

429
00:23:47.051 --> 00:23:48.302
Brody's scum.

430
00:23:48.385 --> 00:23:51.055
Why do people who have money think
they can do whatever they want?

431
00:23:51.138 --> 00:23:52.681
Because they usually can.

432
00:23:54.433 --> 00:23:57.478
You know. did Sawyer's partner mention
the assault when you interviewed her?

433
00:23:57.561 --> 00:24:00.731
No. she was too busy calling me
a true love skeptic.

434
00:24:01.899 --> 00:24:03.150
But she's not wrong.

435
00:24:03.233 --> 00:24:04.735
Okay. you know what?

436
00:24:07.237 --> 00:24:08.697
Hey. this is Amanda.

437
00:24:08.781 --> 00:24:09.865
Hi.

438
00:24:10.616 --> 00:24:12.576
Sounds good. I will see you there.

439
00:24:12.660 --> 00:24:15.371
You know. sooner or later you have
to tell that man your real name.

440
00:24:16.246 --> 00:24:18.499
I am protecting my peace.

441
00:24:18.582 --> 00:24:22.127
Look. if things get serious with Malcolm.
I will tell him the truth.

442
00:24:22.211 --> 00:24:23.212
Cross my heart.

443
00:24:26.757 --> 00:24:29.426
Come on. Doreen. I need Judge Earhart
to sign that warrant.

444
00:24:30.469 --> 00:24:32.638
Yeah. the safe deposit box.
you remembered.

445
00:24:33.847 --> 00:24:36.892
Well. can you move it
to the top of his pile?

446
00:24:38.894 --> 00:24:40.354
Yeah? You promise?

447
00:24:41.021 --> 00:24:42.731
Oh. You're the best.

448
00:24:42.815 --> 00:24:44.233
Hey. you still like those Samoas?

449
00:24:44.316 --> 00:24:47.111
I got some for ya. Four boxes on me.

450
00:24:48.445 --> 00:24:49.446
Thanks. Doreen.

451
00:24:49.530 --> 00:24:52.366
- Wow. you really are working the clerk.
- Told ya.

452
00:24:52.449 --> 00:24:55.077
So. what's going on with the mystery
of Cheetah Mask's mom?

453
00:24:55.160 --> 00:24:58.580
Well. don't want to brag.
but. um. I did cross reference women

454
00:24:58.664 --> 00:25:01.333
with her birth date.
death date and initials.

455
00:25:01.417 --> 00:25:03.210
which has led me to… Guess how many moms.

456
00:25:04.211 --> 00:25:05.754
- Drumroll. please.
- Oh.

457
00:25:08.424 --> 00:25:09.425
One.

458
00:25:10.384 --> 00:25:11.927
Great. Let's go pick up her son.

459
00:25:12.011 --> 00:25:13.846
Uh. not so fast. She has ten kids.

460
00:25:13.929 --> 00:25:15.639
My womb aches for this woman.

461
00:25:21.437 --> 00:25:24.148
Franklin. what's going on
with you and Heller?

462
00:25:24.231 --> 00:25:25.774
You know. it's ugly in there.

463
00:25:25.858 --> 00:25:27.776
But it's for the good.

464
00:25:36.452 --> 00:25:40.539
Hey. you said. uh. 7:00. right?

465
00:25:40.622 --> 00:25:43.292
- Where is everybody?
- Yeah. it's kind of weird. huh?

466
00:25:43.375 --> 00:25:46.128
I-I hope you don't mind. I preordered.

467
00:25:46.837 --> 00:25:50.340
Wait. this is the apple tart tatin
from the restaurant.

468
00:25:51.467 --> 00:25:52.551
Mm-hmm.

469
00:25:54.094 --> 00:25:56.597
Malcolm. did you rent out
this entire theater?

470
00:25:58.015 --> 00:26:00.726
Yeah. Is it too much?

471
00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:03.187
I mean. I'm into it.

472
00:26:05.147 --> 00:26:08.233
Listen. I-I know it's early but…

473
00:26:10.110 --> 00:26:11.361
how this feels…

474
00:26:13.572 --> 00:26:15.282
I just want to see where this can go.

475
00:26:21.830 --> 00:26:24.416
What are we watching?

476
00:26:25.084 --> 00:26:26.960
Shh. It's a surprise.

477
00:26:27.044 --> 00:26:30.798
…long. and then he writes. "You're
a real live wire. Love Mr. Carroll."

478
00:26:30.881 --> 00:26:32.841
You know. it's all so phony.

479
00:26:32.925 --> 00:26:35.094
He wants to leave things
on a good note.

480
00:26:35.177 --> 00:26:38.472
Well. when Mr. Carroll uses
the word love. I look for a new word.

481
00:26:38.555 --> 00:26:39.681
Lloyd.

482
00:26:40.307 --> 00:26:42.434
He lied to me.
He lied to everybody.

483
00:26:43.477 --> 00:26:44.770
I just left home.

484
00:26:48.649 --> 00:26:49.650
I need you.

485
00:26:49.733 --> 00:26:52.236
- Oh. Wait. wait. This is my favorite part.
- What. what?

486
00:26:52.319 --> 00:26:53.362
Okay.

487
00:26:53.445 --> 00:26:55.280
Everything else means nothing to me.

488
00:26:57.157 --> 00:26:58.617
I love you.

489
00:26:58.700 --> 00:27:00.828
How many more times do I have to say it?

490
00:27:05.999 --> 00:27:07.459
I need you.

491
00:27:20.931 --> 00:27:22.933
- Oh.
- Good catch.

492
00:27:23.016 --> 00:27:24.601
We got to go. Eat that.

493
00:27:24.685 --> 00:27:27.896
Ooh. You took a change of clothes
with you this time. You're learning.

494
00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:31.316
Can you please stop talking
about my private. personal. private life?

495
00:27:31.817 --> 00:27:33.151
Fine.

496
00:27:33.235 --> 00:27:34.695
Brody Evans' alibi checked out.

497
00:27:34.778 --> 00:27:39.074
His. uh. smarmy face was all over
the concert jumbotron the whole night.

498
00:27:39.157 --> 00:27:41.034
We need to link it
to Jennings' business partner.

499
00:27:41.118 --> 00:27:43.078
If Sawyer knew
about Brody Evans assaulting Anna.

500
00:27:43.161 --> 00:27:45.622
I don't believe for one second
that Liv didn't know too.

501
00:27:45.706 --> 00:27:49.084
Her spin class instructor said Liv swiped
a card on the bike at the start of class.

502
00:27:49.167 --> 00:27:50.752
Maybe she snuck out.

503
00:28:00.512 --> 00:28:01.805
Well. look who it is.

504
00:28:02.472 --> 00:28:04.641
For two nights in a row.
you don't sleep at the house.

505
00:28:05.642 --> 00:28:07.060
I'm not prorating your rent. you know?

506
00:28:07.144 --> 00:28:09.771
Can everybody stop
minding my business. please?

507
00:28:12.649 --> 00:28:14.359
Oh. excuse me.

508
00:28:16.236 --> 00:28:18.614
- Franklin. where's your sidearm?
- Wouldn't you like to know?

509
00:28:18.697 --> 00:28:20.490
Hey. did you get the warrant
for the safe deposit box?

510
00:28:20.574 --> 00:28:22.409
- What box?
- He's talking to us.

511
00:28:22.492 --> 00:28:23.744
A homicide at a bank heist.

512
00:28:23.827 --> 00:28:26.663
We're on our way to go question the owner
of the safe deposit box right now.

513
00:28:26.747 --> 00:28:27.998
Okay. Superhero.

514
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:31.335
How you feeling. Mama?

515
00:28:31.418 --> 00:28:33.545
Good. Yeah. really good.

516
00:28:33.629 --> 00:28:34.880
- Can I?
- Yeah.

517
00:28:36.131 --> 00:28:37.633
Hi. baby.

518
00:28:37.716 --> 00:28:39.593
It's Aunty Faith. Hi.

519
00:28:41.929 --> 00:28:43.972
Hi.

520
00:28:44.056 --> 00:28:45.349
Oh.

521
00:28:45.432 --> 00:28:46.808
- 'Kay.
- Oh. Okay.

522
00:28:49.311 --> 00:28:50.812
"Wyatt Fernsby."

523
00:28:53.023 --> 00:28:55.233
He only had the safe deposit box
a couple months.

524
00:28:55.317 --> 00:28:57.319
Safe just don't mean
what it used to.

525
00:28:57.402 --> 00:28:59.863
That elevator thing was weird. right?
With Trent?

526
00:28:59.947 --> 00:29:03.450
Yeah. I'm fine. But you know what really
seems to help is not talking about it.

527
00:29:03.533 --> 00:29:04.534
Thank you.

528
00:29:09.998 --> 00:29:11.833
- Mr. Fernsby?
- Oh. crap.

529
00:29:12.834 --> 00:29:13.961
APD.

530
00:29:15.128 --> 00:29:17.339
- I got him. I got him.
- Okay. I'll get an ambulance.

531
00:29:20.300 --> 00:29:23.428
Hey. yeah. Yeah. get an EMS.
You see my location.

532
00:29:24.137 --> 00:29:25.597
His vitals are stable.

533
00:29:25.681 --> 00:29:28.016
You have about five minutes.
He needs to rest.

534
00:29:28.100 --> 00:29:29.685
Okay. Thank you.

535
00:29:31.728 --> 00:29:32.938
Hey. Mr. Fernsby.

536
00:29:33.021 --> 00:29:36.775
we need to ask you some questions about
the contents of that safe deposit box.

537
00:29:36.858 --> 00:29:39.319
You're aware that it was stolen
from First Peachtree Bank?

538
00:29:41.780 --> 00:29:45.659
Listen. someone was killed
during the robbery.

539
00:29:45.742 --> 00:29:48.078
We're trying to figure this out
before anyone else gets hurt.

540
00:29:48.161 --> 00:29:49.287
You can talk to us.

541
00:29:51.665 --> 00:29:55.794
I work for Biosentia Pharmaceuticals.

542
00:29:57.671 --> 00:30:02.134
I was told to shred some documents
but I kept a copy.

543
00:30:02.968 --> 00:30:04.845
It was my insurance policy.

544
00:30:04.928 --> 00:30:06.388
That's what was in the box?

545
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:08.682
Someone from the company
must have found out I took them.

546
00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:12.936
Do you understand
what these people will do to me?

547
00:30:13.020 --> 00:30:15.147
That's why you wanted to end it yourself?

548
00:30:18.650 --> 00:30:22.654
Look. we need you to tell us exactly
what's in those documents.

549
00:30:23.238 --> 00:30:25.323
I'm not saying anything without a lawyer.

550
00:30:27.242 --> 00:30:31.204
Well. Wyatt Fernsby's lawyer wants
to strike a deal with the DA.

551
00:30:32.581 --> 00:30:34.666
- What is he hiding?
- Yeah. no kidding.

552
00:30:34.750 --> 00:30:38.170
Definitely not what I was expecting
for my first day back in the field.

553
00:30:38.253 --> 00:30:40.047
Surprise!

554
00:30:40.130 --> 00:30:42.174
Oho! Wow.

555
00:30:42.257 --> 00:30:45.635
Congratulations. Polaski.
You and that doc are gonna have some kid.

556
00:30:47.095 --> 00:30:49.473
Ooh. Mmm.

557
00:30:50.766 --> 00:30:51.808
It wasn't me.

558
00:30:51.892 --> 00:30:54.978
Oh. It's all right. It's all good.

559
00:30:55.062 --> 00:30:57.564
Thank you. That's… …really…

560
00:30:58.273 --> 00:31:00.108
It's very thoughtful of you.

561
00:31:01.318 --> 00:31:03.403
- You all right. Cap?
- Yeah. I'm all right.

562
00:31:03.487 --> 00:31:05.072
I'm great.

563
00:31:05.155 --> 00:31:07.866
We're gonna get this worked out
and then we're…

564
00:31:07.949 --> 00:31:10.494
We'll get it back to you in…
…tip-top shape.

565
00:31:11.286 --> 00:31:13.121
- We?
- Yeah. we.

566
00:31:13.205 --> 00:31:15.082
- Come on. He ain't got no manual.
- Thank you. Cap.

567
00:31:15.165 --> 00:31:16.416
Why'd you tell 'em that?

568
00:31:16.500 --> 00:31:19.711
You ain't got no manual.
That's why I told her. No. Uh-uh.

569
00:31:19.795 --> 00:31:22.047
- You know we got to take this to Amanda.
- Oh. I know.

570
00:31:22.130 --> 00:31:24.091
Why? 'Cause you can read my mind?
'Cause you have ESP?

571
00:31:24.174 --> 00:31:25.675
I mean. I do.

572
00:31:25.759 --> 00:31:28.762
But also
because our "murder at an ATM" case

573
00:31:28.845 --> 00:31:30.597
just turned into
a corporate espionage plot.

574
00:31:30.680 --> 00:31:35.310
- So. technically we need the GBI.
- Yeah.

575
00:31:40.524 --> 00:31:43.485
The spin instructor said that Liv was
definitely here when the class ended.

576
00:31:43.568 --> 00:31:45.821
She was yelling goodbye
and waving both of her hands

577
00:31:45.904 --> 00:31:48.657
like one of those blow-up things
at the used car dealership.

578
00:31:48.740 --> 00:31:52.702
Hmm. Well. she made a show of leaving
to establish her alibi.

579
00:31:52.786 --> 00:31:53.787
- Yeah.
- "Hey. look at me.

580
00:31:53.870 --> 00:31:55.122
I've been here the whole time."

581
00:31:55.205 --> 00:31:57.082
It's dark in those studios.

582
00:31:57.165 --> 00:31:59.042
No one would notice
if she disappeared for a while.

583
00:31:59.126 --> 00:32:02.796
Only thing is. parking lot attendant
said Liv's car never left.

584
00:32:03.421 --> 00:32:05.924
And Sawyer's house
is almost three miles away.

585
00:32:06.007 --> 00:32:09.052
She knew not to call a car.
Too easy to trace.

586
00:32:09.136 --> 00:32:10.470
Maybe she ran.

587
00:32:11.054 --> 00:32:13.515
Six miles plus the adrenaline
of killing Sawyer.

588
00:32:14.224 --> 00:32:16.476
then jumping back on a spin bike? No.

589
00:32:17.227 --> 00:32:19.604
People would've noticed her
huffing and puffing.

590
00:32:20.522 --> 00:32:23.275
Or she didn't go on foot.

591
00:32:27.696 --> 00:32:29.948
All right.

592
00:32:31.408 --> 00:32:32.659
All right. I'll time you.

593
00:32:32.742 --> 00:32:34.536
- Okay. Ready. set...
- Hold on.

594
00:32:37.372 --> 00:32:39.499
- What are you doing?
- Here.

595
00:32:39.583 --> 00:32:42.169
- Fine. Okay.
- Hmm.

596
00:32:42.252 --> 00:32:43.253
- You need help?
- Nope.

597
00:32:43.336 --> 00:32:45.172
Okay. You sure?

598
00:32:45.255 --> 00:32:46.256
Yes.

599
00:32:46.798 --> 00:32:48.675
- How do I look?
- Good.

600
00:32:48.758 --> 00:32:50.051
Okay. Um…

601
00:32:52.220 --> 00:32:53.388
Eduardo. read text.

602
00:32:53.471 --> 00:32:57.976
Text from Ava.
"Hey. sexy. send me a selfie?"

603
00:32:59.019 --> 00:33:02.189
- Um… One second.
- Uh-huh.

604
00:33:04.441 --> 00:33:06.943
Oh. Will. She is not talking about
that kind of selfie.

605
00:33:08.403 --> 00:33:09.738
What do you mean?

606
00:33:10.447 --> 00:33:12.574
Oh. Oh!

607
00:33:12.657 --> 00:33:13.909
Oh. my. Really?

608
00:33:15.493 --> 00:33:17.370
That's quite forward. Um…

609
00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.457
- I'll respond to her later.
- Okay.

610
00:33:20.540 --> 00:33:23.168
- Shall we start?
- And go.

611
00:33:23.251 --> 00:33:24.586
Bye.

612
00:33:59.704 --> 00:34:00.705
Here we are.

613
00:34:02.457 --> 00:34:07.337
Bang. bang. bang. bang. bang.

614
00:34:11.967 --> 00:34:15.971
Now. would Liv head back
the way she came. or keep going straight?

615
00:34:19.182 --> 00:34:20.684
That hill was a little steep.

616
00:34:21.434 --> 00:34:24.271
Might be faster
if I take another route back to the gym.

617
00:34:24.354 --> 00:34:25.355
Yeah. let's do that.

618
00:34:58.305 --> 00:35:00.682
Seventeen minutes and 34 seconds.

619
00:35:00.765 --> 00:35:01.766
It was her.

620
00:35:02.267 --> 00:35:03.852
I knew I didn't like that woman.

621
00:35:05.020 --> 00:35:08.648
Ms. Summermann. there was one file
your office didn't turn over.

622
00:35:08.732 --> 00:35:11.651
I recently hired a new assistant.
I'll make sure you get that.

623
00:35:11.735 --> 00:35:12.902
I didn't say which file.

624
00:35:14.821 --> 00:35:16.906
But you already know it was Anna Martello.

625
00:35:17.449 --> 00:35:19.492
Did you withhold information
so we wouldn't find out

626
00:35:19.576 --> 00:35:22.037
that Brody Evans assaulted Ms. Martello?

627
00:35:22.120 --> 00:35:25.665
And before you protest.
No. we can't prove there was an assault.

628
00:35:25.749 --> 00:35:29.252
but what we can prove.
from credit card records. eyewitnesses.

629
00:35:29.336 --> 00:35:31.588
texts and so forth. is that Mr. Jennings...

630
00:35:31.671 --> 00:35:33.340
- Rest his soul.
- Truly.

631
00:35:33.923 --> 00:35:35.634
He met Ms. Martello the night he died

632
00:35:35.717 --> 00:35:39.387
then he called Brody Evans and promised
he'd expose him as a rapist.

633
00:35:39.471 --> 00:35:41.181
Sawyer believed Anna and so do we.

634
00:35:41.264 --> 00:35:42.349
Good for you.

635
00:35:42.432 --> 00:35:44.601
What does any of this
have to do with my client?

636
00:35:44.684 --> 00:35:47.270
I was never told about any assault.

637
00:35:47.979 --> 00:35:49.481
Maybe you should look at Anna.

638
00:35:49.564 --> 00:35:50.607
We had that thought too but...

639
00:35:50.690 --> 00:35:53.276
Following Mr. Jennings's phone call
with Brody.

640
00:35:54.110 --> 00:35:59.574
Brody wired over $100.000 to you

641
00:35:59.658 --> 00:36:01.743
"to make Sawyer go away."

642
00:36:01.826 --> 00:36:03.912
That's a direct quote from Brody.
He's in custody.

643
00:36:03.995 --> 00:36:06.623
And surprisingly. that man has no interest
in protecting you.

644
00:36:06.706 --> 00:36:09.125
even with all you did to protect him.

645
00:36:09.209 --> 00:36:10.377
Say nothing else.

646
00:36:10.460 --> 00:36:13.004
By the way. did you drive here
or did you hop on another scooter?

647
00:36:13.088 --> 00:36:15.465
You know. I can't get through
a whole spin class either.

648
00:36:15.548 --> 00:36:18.885
I get why you ducked out.
except you did it to kill your partner.

649
00:36:18.968 --> 00:36:20.970
But you didn't know
about the construction you'd hit

650
00:36:21.054 --> 00:36:23.807
on your way back
from shooting him five times.

651
00:36:24.599 --> 00:36:28.853
Or that there was a camera on that corner.

652
00:36:32.065 --> 00:36:35.652
Liv Summermann. you're under arrest for
the murder for hire of Sawyer Jennings.

653
00:36:35.735 --> 00:36:37.654
Please stand up. hands behind your back.

654
00:36:39.030 --> 00:36:41.074
Maybe you'll find your joy in prison.

655
00:36:42.158 --> 00:36:43.159
Let's go.

656
00:36:54.587 --> 00:36:57.132
Oh. good. You're not going home.
Where's Faith?

657
00:36:57.215 --> 00:36:59.342
She has plans. What do you got?

658
00:36:59.426 --> 00:37:01.344
GBI has been brought in
on a bank heist case.

659
00:37:01.428 --> 00:37:04.389
Polaski and Ormewood caught a body.
Robbers killed the only witness.

660
00:37:04.472 --> 00:37:07.475
Our theory is Biosentia Pharmaceuticals
hired the crew

661
00:37:07.559 --> 00:37:10.520
to retrieve stolen documents
hidden at the bank by an employee.

662
00:37:10.603 --> 00:37:12.939
- Hmm. Tell me about this crew.
- We don't know much.

663
00:37:13.022 --> 00:37:15.400
They've hit major hauls
in three separate states.

664
00:37:15.483 --> 00:37:18.027
They are quick. They are precise.
They never leave a trace.

665
00:37:19.028 --> 00:37:22.365
Oh. so this pharma company hired the best.
We have any leads?

666
00:37:25.285 --> 00:37:27.245
Oh. We have an arm.

667
00:37:27.328 --> 00:37:29.539
We're trying to ID him.
He's definitely on this crew.

668
00:37:29.622 --> 00:37:31.708
We're narrowing it down from ten siblings.

669
00:37:31.791 --> 00:37:34.085
Two are deceased. one is a nun.

670
00:37:34.169 --> 00:37:36.004
The point is we are getting close.

671
00:37:36.087 --> 00:37:39.424
Guys. I've got it. Ow.

672
00:37:39.507 --> 00:37:40.800
I got Cheetah Mask.

673
00:37:40.884 --> 00:37:43.344
- The robbers wear animal masks.
- Got it.

674
00:37:43.428 --> 00:37:46.723
Yeah. and Cheetah Mask's
true identity is Preston Willis.

675
00:37:46.806 --> 00:37:47.932
Tattoos match.

676
00:37:48.016 --> 00:37:49.559
Do you have a last known address?

677
00:37:49.642 --> 00:37:52.187
Yes. I do. Swanky digs in Buckhead.

678
00:37:52.270 --> 00:37:53.521
Well. I doubt he's gonna flip.

679
00:37:53.605 --> 00:37:55.857
We need to follow him.
see if we can sweep up his crew.

680
00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:57.734
Agreed. We've got one shot.

681
00:37:57.817 --> 00:37:59.152
- Surveillance?
- Ooh.

682
00:37:59.235 --> 00:38:01.446
- Me? Me.
- Okay.

683
00:38:01.529 --> 00:38:02.781
Will. you and Ormewood.

684
00:38:02.864 --> 00:38:05.492
What?

685
00:38:06.326 --> 00:38:08.119
- I'm driving.
- Let's go.

686
00:38:08.203 --> 00:38:09.788
- Shotgun.
- Obviously.

687
00:38:18.213 --> 00:38:20.757
Grill's going.
He's gotta be coming back out soon.

688
00:38:28.556 --> 00:38:31.768
So. what is this
about you having superpowers?

689
00:38:34.270 --> 00:38:37.440
Well. ever since I finished chemo.
I feel better.

690
00:38:38.191 --> 00:38:40.944
I mean. not throwing up is always awesome.

691
00:38:41.027 --> 00:38:42.153
I appreciate that.

692
00:38:42.237 --> 00:38:43.279
It just…

693
00:38:43.363 --> 00:38:44.864
seems like everything's heightened.

694
00:38:45.532 --> 00:38:48.243
I don't know.
I'm probably just imagining it.

695
00:38:50.370 --> 00:38:52.372
I wouldn't dismiss it.

696
00:38:52.455 --> 00:38:55.250
I mean. your whole identity
is "masculine guy."

697
00:38:55.333 --> 00:38:57.252
What? No. I…

698
00:38:58.545 --> 00:38:59.546
Okay. maybe.

699
00:38:59.629 --> 00:39:00.797
No. look. my point is.

700
00:39:00.880 --> 00:39:03.967
that identity was challenged
when your body stopped cooperating.

701
00:39:04.050 --> 00:39:07.512
Now you're on the other side of it.
feeling better than before.

702
00:39:08.137 --> 00:39:09.138
I get it.

703
00:39:11.015 --> 00:39:13.184
Thanks. weirdo.

704
00:39:17.480 --> 00:39:19.566
You know. Faith
hasn't been sleeping at home.

705
00:39:19.649 --> 00:39:21.526
Tonight will be three days in a row.

706
00:39:21.609 --> 00:39:23.945
Well. she keeps saying it's nothing.
but it's something.

707
00:39:24.028 --> 00:39:26.197
- Yeah. No. who's she think she's fooling?
- Not us.

708
00:39:26.281 --> 00:39:27.782
Not us.

709
00:39:30.660 --> 00:39:31.911
But if she's happy…

710
00:39:35.081 --> 00:39:36.416
She seem happy to you?

711
00:39:37.667 --> 00:39:38.668
Very.

712
00:39:41.087 --> 00:39:42.672
Oh. He's coming outside.

713
00:40:01.983 --> 00:40:04.152
Oh. no.

714
00:40:04.819 --> 00:40:06.779
- You see what I got? Okay. nice little…
- Look at you.

715
00:40:06.863 --> 00:40:09.657
- Yeah. yeah. we getting healthy over here.
- Okay.

716
00:40:09.741 --> 00:40:10.658
A little asparagus.

717
00:40:10.783 --> 00:40:12.285
some shrimp. some protein.

718
00:40:12.368 --> 00:40:13.745
- Nice. Nice.
- Yeah.

719
00:40:13.828 --> 00:40:15.663
Oh. Um…

720
00:40:15.747 --> 00:40:16.748
Hi. this is Amanda.

721
00:40:16.831 --> 00:40:18.917
I need you to get
somewhere private right now.

722
00:40:19.000 --> 00:40:20.376
Sorry. this is work.

723
00:40:20.460 --> 00:40:21.794
Oh. no worries. I'll get the chairs.

724
00:40:21.878 --> 00:40:23.630
Be right back.

725
00:40:23.713 --> 00:40:25.214
Will. what do you want? I'm busy.

726
00:40:25.298 --> 00:40:28.968
I need to tell you something.
Ormewood and Angie's bank heist case…

727
00:40:30.011 --> 00:40:34.140
Malcolm. your Malcolm.
he's part of that crew.

728
00:40:35.975 --> 00:40:38.978
Look. there's no question. okay?
He's dangerous.

729
00:40:41.230 --> 00:40:42.690
No. Wait. that's…

730
00:40:44.192 --> 00:40:45.193
You're wrong.

731
00:40:46.277 --> 00:40:48.613
- You're wrong.
- Look. I'm sorry.

732
00:40:48.696 --> 00:40:50.114
Faith. Faith.

733
00:40:51.449 --> 00:40:53.242
Faith. he's coming back out now.

734
00:40:53.993 --> 00:40:57.413
Faith. he cannot know that we're on
to him. all right?

735
00:40:57.497 --> 00:40:58.706
- Do you hear me?
- Got it.

736
00:40:59.415 --> 00:41:02.710
- Faith.
- I understand. Okay.

737
00:41:02.794 --> 00:41:04.379
- Okay?
- Yeah.

738
00:41:04.462 --> 00:41:05.755
All right. Mm.

739
00:41:08.007 --> 00:41:09.008
Okay.

740
00:41:10.259 --> 00:41:12.512
Got the wine glasses.

740
00:41:13.305 --> 00:42:13.408
